🛠️ What are Build Tools?
👉 Build tools are tools that automate the process of building your application

Building a project includes:
- Compiling code (Java → bytecode)
- Managing dependencies (libraries like Spring, Hibernate)
- Running tests
- Packaging (JAR/WAR file)
- Running the application

👉 Doing all this manually = nightmare 😵
👉 Build tools automate everything ✅

⚙️ Popular Build Tools in Java
1. Maven (Most Common)
👉 Uses pom.xml

Example:
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
</dependency>

✔️ Features:
- Easy to understand
- Huge ecosystem
- Standard structure

2. Gradle (Modern & Faster)
👉 Uses build.gradle

Example:
implementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web'

✔️ Features:
- Faster than Maven
- Less verbose
- More flexible

🔄 What Build Tools Actually Do (Flow)
1. Read config file (pom.xml / build.gradle)
2. Download dependencies
3. Compile code
4. Run tests
5. Package into .jar
6. Run app